PART I: THE AUTOPSY OF THE OLD WORLD
The global financial system is mathematically dead. Not metaphorically. Mathematically.
The Debt Spiral
The world owes three times more than it earns.
Total Sovereign Debt: $338 Trillion
Global GDP: $105 Trillion
Debt-to-GDP Ratio: 322%
The interest alone exceeds the GDP of most nations. The system cannot pay principal. It can only service interest by printing more debt. This is not a cycle. It is a death spiral.
The Zero Labor Crisis
If inflation was the only problem, maybe you could work harder to beat it. But a second beast has arrived: Automation.
AI automation will displace 2 billion jobs by 2040.
Current labor force: 3.5 billion.
Displaced workers: 57% of global labor.
The existing economy requires labor-for-wages. When labor vanishes, wages vanish. When wages vanish, purchasing power vanishes. There is no "retraining" solution at this scale. The math does not permit the survival of the current model.
Conclusion: The current system is mathematically unsalvageable. Any solution requiring permission from the system's architects is no solution at all.
